  "prompt": "My father coming from kanpur on nanded got 6:30 hr late and now no where to go as he has to come to bti on punjab mail. Who is responsible for that?",
  "response": "I understand your frustration regarding the delay and inconvenience caused by your father's journey. Train delays can be caused by a variety of factors including technical issues, weather conditions, track maintenance, or operational challenges. The exact responsibility can be hard to pinpoint without more detailed information.\n\nFor specific complaints about railway delays, you can contact the relevant railway authorities or customer service. Here are some steps you can take:\n\n1. **Contact Railway Authorities**: Reach out to the Indian Railways helpline or customer service. You can usually find contact information on their official website or railway app.\n\n2. **Lodge a Complaint**: Many railway stations have customer service desks where you can lodge a formal complaint detailing the issues faced.\n\n3. **Follow Social Media and Online Platforms**: Indian Railways is active on social media platforms like Twitter. You can tweet at them for quicker responses.\n\n4. **Change Travel Plans**: Given the delay, you might want to check the schedule for the next available trains from Nanded to Bhatinda (BTI) and adjust your plans accordingly.\n\nWhile delays can happen, it's valuable to stay informed about train schedules and alterations through official railway channels to minimize inconvenience.",
